---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../consts';

const title = 'Advertiser Disclosure';
const description =
  'How ITINLending.net makes money: lender referrals, affiliate links, and advertising. Our compensation never costs you anything or changes our editorial guidance.';
const updated = 'June 27, 2026';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/disclosure">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <span class="tag">Legal</span>
      <h1 style="margin-top:10px">Advertiser Disclosure</h1>
      <p class="byline">Last updated {updated}</p>

      <p>
        {SITE.legalName} is an independent publisher operated by
        {SITE.publisher.name} ("we," "us," "our"). The guides, comparisons, and
        lender-matching on this site are free to use because we earn money from a
        small number of advertising and affiliate relationships. This page
        explains exactly how we get paid, who pays us, and, most importantly,
        the firewall we keep between that money and what we tell you. It is
        written to comply with the U.S. Federal Trade Commission's
        <em>Guides Concerning the Use of Endorsements and Testimonials in
        Advertising</em> (16 CFR Part 255), which require any "material
        connection" between a publisher and a product it recommends to be
        disclosed clearly and conspicuously.
      </p>

      <h2>How we earn revenue</h2>
      <p>
        We have a few revenue streams, and every page on this site is funded by
        one or more of them:
      </p>
      <ul class="lead-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Lender and partner referrals.</strong> When you submit our
          qualification form and we connect you with a third-party lender or
          financing partner, we may receive a referral fee or be paid when you
          complete an application or fund a loan. The form passes your request to
          a matching partner; what you submit is used to connect you with lenders
          that work with ITIN holders.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Affiliate links through Commission Junction (CJ).</strong>
          Many of our outbound "apply" and "get matched" links to specific
          lenders, credit cards, and financing products are affiliate links
          served through the Commission Junction (CJ Affiliate) network. When you
          click one of these links and then qualify, sign up, or open an account,
          the advertiser pays us a commission. The link carries a tracking code
          that tells CJ the referral came from us; it does not transmit your
          personal information to us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Affiliate display advertising through Awin.</strong> Some of
          the banner units on the site, including the Credit Karma unit you may
          see on certain pages, are served through the Awin affiliate network. We
          are paid when you click the unit and complete an action on the
          advertiser's site (for example, signing up for a free account). These
          units are always labeled "Advertisement."
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Display advertising through Google AdSense.</strong> On our
          educational articles we run contextual display ads served by Google
          AdSense and its partners. We are paid based on impressions and clicks.
          We do not control which specific advertiser appears in an AdSense slot,
          Google's system selects those, and their presence is not an
          endorsement by us.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How compensation affects (and does not affect) what you read</h2>
      <p>
        This is the part that matters most. Being paid by an advertiser can
        influence <em>which</em> products and lenders we choose to write about
        and <em>where</em> on a page a product link appears. It does
        <strong>not</strong> change the facts we report, the trade-offs we
        disclose, or our assessment of whether a product is right for a given
        situation. We do not accept payment to change a recommendation, to remove
        a drawback from a comparison, or to call a weak product a strong one.
        Our editorial conclusions are reached before, and independently of, any
        commercial arrangement, and they would read exactly the same if we earned
        nothing from them.
      </p>

      <h2>How we select and rank products</h2>
      <p>
        Products, lenders, and financing options are chosen for coverage based on
        how relevant and accessible they are to ITIN holders, specifically
        whether a lender accepts an ITIN in place of a Social Security Number, its
        documentation and down-payment requirements, its real costs and rate
        ranges, and how suitable it is for someone borrowing without an SSN or a
        long U.S. credit history. A product is never included simply because it
        pays the highest commission, and a relevant option is never excluded
        simply because it pays us nothing or has no affiliate program at all.
        Where we compare options, the attributes in our tables (down payments,
        rate ranges, documentation, fees) reflect publicly documented lender
        terms, which can change; we tell you to verify the current terms directly
        with the lender before you apply.
      </p>

      <h2>What this means for you</h2>
      <ul class="lead-list">
        <li>
          <strong>It is never a cost to you.</strong> Our compensation comes from
          advertisers and partners, not from you. You never pay more for a loan,
          card, or product because you reached it through one of our links, and
          the price and terms you get are the same as if you had gone to the
          lender directly.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We do not cover every option.</strong> This site does not
          include every lender, loan program, or financial product in the market.
          Absence from our site is not a judgment about a product.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>We are not the lender.</strong> All loans, mortgages, and
          credit products are offered by third parties under their own terms,
          eligibility rules, and applicable law. Approval, rates, and features are
          set by the lender, not by us.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Our editorial promise</h2>
      <p>
        Opinions, comparisons, and recommendations are our own. They are not
        provided, reviewed, approved, or endorsed by any advertiser, affiliate
        network, lender, or partner. Our research process, how we source from
        primary materials and review guides for accuracy, is described on our
        <a href="/editorial-policy">editorial policy page</a>. We aim to give you
        accurate, useful information so you can make your own decision. If we ever
        get something wrong, <a href="/contact">tell us</a> and we will correct
        it.
      </p>

      <h2>Not financial advice</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on this site is financial, legal, tax, or immigration advice, and
        we are not a bank, lender, mortgage broker, credit-repair organization, or
        financial advisor. We do not originate loans, set rates, or make credit
        decisions. Always confirm current rates, terms, and eligibility directly
        with the lender before you apply. See our
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Use</a> and <a href="/privacy">Privacy
        Policy</a> for more.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
